description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trusts &amp; Grants Officer - 37.5 hours per week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt; £23,375 - £27,104 per annum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Trust &amp; Grants Officer, to work closely with the Trust &amp; Grants Manager, who will contribute fully to the development and delivery of the Trusts &amp; Grants  income line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have joint responsibility for the preparation and submission of grant funding applications for up to five and six figure gifts to charitable trusts and foundations, running a first class stewardship programme including impact and other reporting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following an Appeals based approach, you will specifically liaise with charitable trusts &amp; foundations to identify best fit between projects and funders, building relationships with a view to optimising success rates; gather and collate project information and assimilate into trust and grant funding applications; prepare and submit funding applications including costings; produce and plan reports on outcomes within required deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Along with an ongoing commitment to education and training, other benefits include a work place pension or the option to continue with an NHS pensions if already contributing, on-site free parking, cycle to work scheme, access to Simply Health (health cash plan), access to EAP (Employee Assist Programme), subsidised meals in our restaurant, and the opportunity to purchase annual leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you wish to apply, please complete an application form. CV&#96;s received in isolation will not be considered for interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date is Sunday 15th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to promoting equality of opportunity across our workforce and particularly welcome applications from minority groups&lt;/p&gt;
